  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0db9\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dda \u0d91\u0dc5\u0dc0\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vegetable prices down in Dambulla",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Farmers, traders and intermediate businessmen say that the prices of vegetables in Dambulla Economic Center are decreasing these days while wholesale and retail vegetable prices are increasing in vegetable shops all over the island.",
        "The traders further pointed out that the Dambulla Economic Center is getting a large harvest of vegetables from all over the island these days and compared to that, the prices of vegetables are decreasing due to the decrease in the number of traders coming to buy vegetables. They point out that upland vegetables such as beans, leeks, carrots and cabbage are sold at less than fifty per cent per kilo in the Mbulla Economic Centre.",
        "The farmers also point out that the beans which were sold at a high price between 550 and 600 rupees, are sold at a price between 220-300 rupees and a kilo of leeks are sold at 100 rupees.",
        "They point out that every vegetable except chilli eggplant is sold for 50% less than the prevailing price and they have to stay all day and sell the vegetables at very low prices without being able to sell them.",
        "The wholesale price of a kilo of vegetables at the Dambulla Economic Center this afternoon (Rs.)"
      ],
